addr="jonmsterling"
title="Jon Sterling">Jon Sterling</fr:link></fr:author></fr:authors><fr:parent>jms-00X1</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We can define a macro to compute the bibliography of a given tree, making use of <fr:code><![CDATA[\query/transclusion-coslice]]></fr:code> from <fr:ref
addr="jms-00X4"
href="jms-00X4.xml"
taxon="Example" />.</fr:p><fr:pre><![CDATA[\def\query/bibliography[x]{
 \open\query
 \isect{
  \union-fam{\transclusion-coslice{\x}}{\edges}{\outgoing}{\rel/links}
 }{
  \taxon{reference}
 }
}]]></fr:pre><fr:p>The above code first accumulates all the outgoing links from the given tree and any of its children, and then restricts (by intersection) to those with taxon <fr:code>reference</fr:code>.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter><fr:tree
